				"title":"Information about sending money using the Japan Post Bank deposit card",
				"pubDate":"Wed, 19 Jun 2013 06:56:00 +0000",
				"feed_href":"http://brastelremit04.wordpress.com/2013/06/19/information-about-sending-money-using-the-japan-post-bank-deposit-card/",
				"ctgy":"IMPORTANT",
				"content":"<p>The Japan Post Bank deposit card you receive when registering an Easy Transfer account after selecting Japan Post Bank as deposit method can be used only through the:<br /> <strong>Japan Post Bank ATMs:</strong> By inserting the deposit card into the machine, or<br /> <strong>Japan Post Bank counters:</strong> By presenting the deposit card and the deposit form filled in.<br /> In both cases, the money has to be deposited in cash.</p> <p><strong>Note that if the deposit is made through Internet banking or any other method other than the ones mentioned above, the transfer will not be processed and additional procedures will be required.</strong></p> <p>To make deposits using Internet banking, or to deposit directly from your Japan Post Bank account, please select Mizuho Bank as deposit method.</p> <p>Please contact customer service if you have any questions.</p> <br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/brastelremit04.wordpress.com/260/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/brastelremit04.wordpress.com/260/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=brastelremit04.wordpress.com&#038;blog=33283832&#038;post=260&#038;subd=brastelremit04&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />"
